The paper deals with the problem of secure communication in the presence of an eavesdropper, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of coding schemes, which is relevant to networked information systems (cs.NI) and secure computation (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses numerical results to establish the secure capacity region, which involves computational methods and algorithms (cs.DS).
